        <!-- último -->
        <div class="py-10">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-8 bg-white rounded-t-lg h-full">
                <div
                    class="w-full p-10 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-20 justify-center items-start"
                >
                    <div class="w-full">
                        <h2
                            class="text-lg md:text-xl text-blueMain text-center font-bold"
                        >
                            Evaluate the Plant's Technical Specifications
                        </h2>
                        <div class="w-full bg-grisT h-[1px] my-3"></div>
                        <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin text-grisT">
                            Ensure the plant you choose aligns with your
                            production goals, including mix capacity, fuel
                            efficiency, and environmental compliance. Advanced
                            features like modern control systems or capabilities
                            for RAP integration can enhance productivity and
                            reduce costs.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="w-full">
                        <h2
                            class="text-lg md:text-xl text-blueMain text-center font-bold"
                        >
                            Analyze Long-Term Costs
                        </h2>
                        <div class="w-full bg-grisT h-[1px] my-3"></div>
                        <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin text-grisT">
                            Initial cost is just one aspect of your investment.
                            Assess maintenance expenses, spare parts
                            availability, and energy consumption over the
                            plant's lifecycle. Reliable manufacturers often
                            provide a clear breakdown of these costs.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="w-full">
                        <h2
                            class="text-lg md:text-xl text-blueMain text-center font-bold"
                        >
                            Understand the Supplier’s Support
                        </h2>
                        <div class="w-full bg-grisT h-[1px] my-3"></div>
                        <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin text-grisT">
                            After-sales service can be as important as the plant
                            itself. Confirm the availability of technical
                            support, operator training, and prompt delivery of
                            spare parts. Suppliers with strong service networks
                            can save you significant downtime.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="w-full">
                        <h2
                            class="text-lg md:text-xl text-blueMain text-center font-bold"
                        >
                            Inspect the Manufacturing Quality
                        </h2>
                        <div class="w-full bg-grisT h-[1px] my-3"></div>
                        <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin text-grisT">
                            Focus on the durability and material standards,
                            particularly the steel used in construction. Verify
                            certifications that ensure the alloy's purity and
                            quality. High-grade materials are essential for
                            plants built for heavy-duty applications, as they
                            provide superior longevity and can endure demanding
                            operational conditions
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="w-full">
                        <h2
                            class="text-lg md:text-xl text-blueMain text-center font-bold"
                        >
                            Examine the Environmental Compliance
                        </h2>
                        <div class="w-full bg-grisT h-[1px] my-3"></div>
                        <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin text-grisT">
                            Regulations around emissions are becoming stricter
                            globally. Choose a plant that not only meets current
                            standards but is also prepared for future
                            requirements.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="w-full">
                        <h2
                            class="text-lg md:text-xl text-blueMain text-center font-bold"
                        >
                            Check Proven Performance
                        </h2>
                        <div class="w-full bg-grisT h-[1px] my-3"></div>
                        <p class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin text-grisT">
                            Ask suppliers for case studies or site visits where
                            their plants are operational. Speak with existing
                            customers to understand their experiences regarding
                            reliability, efficiency, and support.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div
                class="max-w-7xl mx-auto rounded-b-lg flex justify-center bg-white py-16"
            >
                <div class="w-4/6">
                    <p
                        class="text-base md:text-lg font-thin text-grisT text-center"
                    >
                        Remember, an asphalt plant is the backbone of your
                        operation. Investing time in due diligence now ensures a
                        smoother production process and long-term profitability.
                        Reach out to us for personalized guidance—we're here to
                        help you make an informed decision.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="max-w-7xl px-8 mx-auto">
            <GallerySlider client:only slides={binSlides2} visibleThumbs={6} />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
